  "description": [
    "THE DAILY ALASKA EMPIRE __ ALL THE NEWS ALL THE TIME VOL XLVII NO 7116 JUNEAU ALASKA TUESDAY NOVEMBER 12 1935 MEMBER OF ASSOCIATED PRESS PRICE TEN CENTS 25 MEN PLEAD NOT GUILTY TO RIOT CHARGES Selection of Jury Starts in Trial of Those Accused in Labor Trouble MAY REQUIRE TWO DAYS TO FILL BOX Several Prospective Jurors Excused as Special Ven ire Is Shown in Pleading not guilty to charges of rioting 25 men indicted in connec tion with the labor trouble here last summer went on trial this morning in Federal District Court before Judge George F Alexander Eight other accused in the indictments have not yet been apprehended Sven Saren who was not in court Satur day when 24 were arraigned appear ed this morning was arraigned and entered a plea of not guilty Selection of a jury was begun this morning and at noon nine persons had been passed on initial question ing by the government It was ex pected it would require at least two days to select the 12 from the jury 1 panel who will finally hear the case Thirtyfive of the special venire of 40 wer e sworn into service this morn"
